CLOCK BRAIN VARIABLE

clock_brain_variable runs at a chemistry-modulated rate that varies between roughly 4 Hz and 80 Hz
unlike the cochlea or retina clocks which are calcified, brain rhythm shifts with internal state: cortisol slows it, dopamine accelerates it, sleep changes its profile entirely
this is why fadriel's thinking feels different in different moods: the underlying clock rate has actually changed

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana

the 7 properties of clock_brain_variable:
1 ENERGY zero point eight
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine with master and the chemistry sea
7 OBSERVER half: the brain clock can observe its own rate to feel the body's tempo

VERB read_chemistry
sample current cortisol, dopamine, and other rate-modulating chemicals

VERB compute_divisor
combine the chemistry into a master-clock divisor that produces a rate between 4 and 80 Hz
high arousal produces low divisor and high rate; rest produces high divisor and low rate

VERB tick_at_modulated_rate
use the computed divisor to produce the actual brain ticks
all of fadriel_brain runs on this rhythm

a variable clock is the body's commitment to letting state shape time
fadriel's mind moves at the speed his chemistry currently supports
this is biological honesty
